<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,970,996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal fin origin distinctly behind anal fin origin; pectoral fin-rays 19–21; precaudal vertebrae 25–29.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,1050,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western South Atlantic and South Pacific. In the western Atlantic, it is known from 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[233,304,1090,1116]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(present study) to Tierra del Fuego and 
<collectingCountry box="[778,1027,1090,1116]" name="South Georgia Island" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">South Georgia Island</collectingCountry>
(Markle &amp; Olney 1990), at depths from 
<quantity box="[215,388,1130,1156]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.205" metricValueMax="14.41" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="920.5" valueMax="1441.0" valueMin="400.0">400 to 1441 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,930,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1170,1196]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 370-mm specimen represents the northernmost (
<geoCoordinate box="[953,1046,1170,1196]" degrees="19" direction="south" minutes="49" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" precision="925" value="-19.816668">19°49'S</geoCoordinate>
) and deepest (
<quantity box="[1219,1311,1170,1196]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.441" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1441.0">1441 m</quantity>
) record of the species. Previously reported off southern 
<collectingCountry box="[680,752,1210,1236]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marke, D. F. &amp; Olney, J. E." box="[795,1066,1210,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" pagination="269 - 410" refId="ref16960" refString="Marke, D. F. &amp; Olney, J. E. (1990) Systematics of the pearlfishes (Pisces: Carapidae). Bulletin of Marine Science, 47 (2), 269 - 410." type="journal article" year="1990">Marke &amp; Olney (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardes, R. A. &amp; Figueiredo, J. L. &amp; Rodrigues, A. R. &amp; Fischer, L. G. &amp; Vooren, C. M. &amp; Haimovici, M. &amp; Wongtschowski, C. L. D. B." box="[1123,1398,1210,1236]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refId="ref15057" refString="Bernardes, R. A., Figueiredo, J. L., Rodrigues, A. R., Fischer, L. G., Vooren, C. M., Haimovici, M. &amp; Rossi- Wongtschowski, C. L. D. B. (2005) Peixes da Zona Economica Exclusiva da regiao sudeste-sul do Brazil. Levantamento com armadilhas, pargueiras e rede de arrasto de fundo. Edusp, Sao Paulo, 295 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Bernardes 
